This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with improving latent representations of images. The use of auto-encoder-based framework and classifiers also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of image manipulation and generation indicates that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of semi-supervised learning suggests that it could belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
